<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>io.github.chimi6.limelight-linux-elgato-lights-controller</id>
  <name>LimeLight</name>
  <summary>Lightweight controller for Elgato Key Lights</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      LimeLight is a lightweight Elgato Key Light controller for Linux. It discovers Key Lights on your LAN and lets you
      control power, brightness, and color temperature without the bloat.
    </p>
    <p>
      It runs a small local helper daemon that talks to the lights and exposes a localhost HTTP API so you can build your
      own integrations (like an Open Deck plugin).
    </p>
  </description>
